utcomes. Instead, he contends, we should strive to simply understand the principles by which phenomena are produced. For Hayek this modesty of aspirations went hand in hand with his concern over widespread enthusiasm for economic planning. As a result, these essays are relevant to ongoing debates within the social sciences and to discussion about the role government can and should play in the economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aSaint-Simonianism. 0aSocial sciencesxMethodology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  areason, rationality, cognition, mental health, illness, deterioration, individualism, humanity, society, science, henri de saint-simon, comte, enfantin, hegel, nonfiction, philosophy, psychology, social sciences, sociology, research, methodology, theory, socialism, politics, collectivism, economics, economy, finance, secularism.1 aCaldwell, Bruce, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226321127423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226321127/original  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles